\f2 M M AT: Shared primitive variable "doorOpen" in one thread may not yield the value of the most recent write from another thread\'a0 At Controller.java:[line 125]
\f1 \

\f2 Analysis: Since multiple threads (the timer and the user input) are looking at the door status, one thread might see an old "cached" value instead of the latest change. This happens because the variable isn't marked as volatile, which would force threads to always fetch the most recent version from memory.
\f1 \
\

\f2 M M AT: Shared primitive variable "powerLevel" in one thread may not yield the value of the most recent write from another thread\'a0 At Controller.java:[line 38]
\f1 \

\f2 Analysis: Similar to the door status, the power level might not be updated correctly across different threads. If the main thread changes the power while the timer thread is running, the timer might keep cooking with the old power level because it hasn't "seen" the update yet.
\f1 \
