\f2 M M IS: Inconsistent synchronization of microwave.Controller.mode; locked 58% of time\'a0 Unsynchronized access at Controller.java:[line 127]
\f1 \

\f2 Analysis: The mode variable is sometimes used inside a synchronized block and sometimes not, which can lead to data races. This specific warning points out that an assertion is checking the mode without holding a lock, meaning the mode could change right while it's being checked.
